Project 1  
Analysis of 1 selected use cases

| use case name | Remote Telescope Monitoring |
| :---- | :---- |
| actor | Astronomer,Telescope Operator |
| Preconditions | The user has logged into the system and has the corresponding monitoring permissions. The telescope is in operation, allowing remote monitoring. |
| Postconditions | Users can view the operational status and observation data of the telescope in real-time. The system continuously updates monitoring information and provides log records. |
| Main Flow | The user logs into the system and navigates to the telescope monitoring interface. The user selects the telescope to be monitored and requests a connection. The system establishes a remote connection and displays real-time status information (such as telescope location, environmental data, current observation tasks, etc.). Users can view detailed logs and historical data. The user chooses to exit the monitoring interface, and the system closes the real-time monitoring session. |
| Alternative Flow | connection failed If the telescope is not in operation or the network connection is abnormal, the system will prompt an error. Users can try reconnecting or contacting the administrator. |
